{{!--
  Maintainer notes (not emitted in G-code):
  - 4-axis Fanuc post template — A-axis rotary (rotation around X by default).
  - Uses standard Fanuc G-code conventions: G21 metric, G90 absolute, G17 XY plane.
  - Comments use Fanuc parentheses format: (COMMENT TEXT).
  - No G43.4 RTCP — 4-axis indexed/continuous work does not require RTCP on most
    Fanuc controls. If your setup needs tool-center-point control, use the 5-axis post.
  - G93 inverse-time feed mode is supported via the inverseTimeFeed context flag.
  - When enabled, G93 is emitted before toolpath and G94 is restored after.
  - Template context keys: resources/posts/README.md (PostContext / renderPost).
  - Additional context for 4-axis: axisCount, aAxisRangeDeg, aAxisOrientation.
--}}
